						               													<description>FEUD: The Seer&amp;rsquo;s Prophecy is a two player competitive tactical strategy card game that transports the players back in time to the Viking Age where they will each take on the role as Commanders of neighboring villages. The Seer&amp;rsquo;s Prophecy have convinced them that they must overthrow each other to save their villages from the gods wrath. As Commanders, players move their units between zones on their turns to recruit units, gather knowledge, set up attacks and defense, and to earn silver to support these activities. Unlike most card games, in FEUD both players use identical decks and may select any card(s) from their deck on their turn thus eliminating the randomness of a typical shuffled deck of cards. This allows for significantly more reliable advanced strategies and makes dynamic counter-play a core component to success. The first player to defeat the opponent's Commander wins the game.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;-description from designer&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
